	<h1>March for Science</h1>

	<p> The United States has a long history of social and political movements that have led to major protests throughout the country including the March for Science, which began on Saturday, April 22, 2017. It occurred in various cities and was sparked by: Support for scientific research and evidence-based policy. The protest led to increased public awareness of the importance of science.</p>

